# Smoke Test — Reproducible Verification

**Agent rule:** After completing code changes, run `npm run smoke` to verify unit tests and build pass before finishing.

**Purpose:** Before committing or after significant changes, run the smoke test to ensure the app builds and core logic passes. Use this for agents and team members.

**RULE (for Cursor agents):** After completing code changes that affect frontend build or core logic, run `npm run smoke` before finishing. If smoke fails, fix the issues before reporting completion.

## Command

```bash
npm run smoke
```

This runs `npm run test && npm run build` (unit tests + production build).

## What it verifies

- **Unit tests:** Utils (`fileValidation`, `validation`), hooks (`useOrderFlow`), components (`CategoryPill`)
- **Build:** Vite production build succeeds (catches TS errors, missing deps, broken imports)

## When to run

- After code changes before pushing
- After pulling/merging from main
- When onboarding (confirms env and deps work)

## Full E2E (optional)

For full browser E2E (auth, profile, tickets):

```bash
npm run test:e2e
```

Requires dev server; use when validating critical user flows. Not part of the default smoke command.
